method_colors <- c("Black", beyonce_colors[c(3, 4, 6, 2, 1)])
names(method_colors) <- method_names
method_shapes <- c(20, 0, 1, 2, 12, 13)
names(method_shapes) <- method_names

Noise simulation

\[\begin{eqnarray} & X_i \sim U[0,1]^d \\ &\pi_1(X) = \mathbf{1}(X^1 \leq 0.5)0.9\\ &H_i \mid X_i \sim \text{Bernoulli}(\pi_1(X_i))\\ &P_i \mid H_i = 0, X_i \sim U[0,1]\\ &P_i \mid H_i = 1, X_i \sim Beta(0.25, 1) \end{eqnarray}\] Note parameter \(d\) in the first line. Hereafter, dimension = \(d\).

Load result files

# Set the directory path
directory <- "simulation/data"

# List all the files in the directory
files <- list.files(here(directory))

# Extract the date from the file names
dates <- stringr::str_extract(files, "\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}")
dates <- as.Date(dates)

# Identify the latest date for files ending with "_eval_high_dim_sim.Rds"
latest_date_sim <- max(dates[grep("_eval_high_dim_sim.Rds", files)], na.rm = TRUE)

# Identify the latest date for files ending with "_eval_high_dim_sim_adapt.Rds"
latest_date_adapt <- max(dates[grep("_eval_high_dim_sim_adapt.Rds", files)], na.rm = TRUE)

# Filter files with the latest date for "_eval_high_dim_sim.Rds"
latest_files_sim <- files[dates == latest_date_sim & grep("_eval_high_dim_sim.Rds", files)]
## Warning in dates == latest_date_sim & grep("_eval_high_dim_sim.Rds", files):
## longer object length is not a multiple of shorter object length
latest_files_sim <- na.omit(latest_files_sim)

# Filter files with the latest date for "_eval_high_dim_sim_adapt.Rds"
latest_files_adapt <- files[dates == latest_date_adapt & grep("_eval_high_dim_sim_adapt.Rds", files)]
latest_files_adapt <- na.omit(latest_files_adapt)

# Read and combine the files with the latest date for "_eval_high_dim_sim.Rds" using purrr and rbindlist
high_dim_res_sim <- map_dfr(latest_files_sim, ~ readRDS(here(directory, .x)))

# Read and combine the files with the latest date for "_eval_high_dim_sim_adapt.Rds" using purrr and rbindlist
high_dim_res_adapt <- map_dfr(latest_files_adapt, ~ readRDS(here(directory, .x)))


# ... (previous code remains the same)

# Row-bind high_dim_res_adapt and high_dim_res_sim
high_dim_res <- rbind(high_dim_res_adapt, high_dim_res_sim)

noise_sim_res <- high_dim_res
noise_sim_res <- noise_sim_res %>% mutate(method = forcats::fct_recode(method,
  "IHW-Quantile" = "IHW-quantile",
  "IHW-Forest" = "IHW-forest"
))
noise_sim_res <- noise_sim_res %>%
  group_by(dimension, method) %>%
  summarize(
    FDR = mean(FDP, na.rm = TRUE),
    Power = mean(pow, na.rm = TRUE),
    # Power_lower = quantile() #TODO
    n_monte_carlo = sum(!is.na(FDP)),
    pow_se = sd(pow, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n_monte_carlo)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

noise_sim_res %>% 
  arrange(n_monte_carlo)

Plot FDR

noise_sim_res_FDR <- ggplot(noise_sim_res, aes(x = dimension, y = FDR, shape = method, col = method)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = alpha, linetype = 2) +
  guides(
    color = guide_legend(nrow=2, title = "Method", legend.text = element_text(size = 4)),
    shape = guide_legend(nrow=2, title = "Method", legend.text = element_text(size = 4)),
    nrow=2
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks())

Small region simulation

\[\begin{eqnarray} & X_i \sim U[0,l] \\ &\pi_1(X) = \mathbf{1}(X^1 \leq 1)0.9\\ &H_i \mid X_i \sim \text{Bernoulli}(\pi_1(X_i))\\ &P_i \mid H_i = 0, X_i \sim U[0,1]\\ &P_i \mid H_i = 1, X_i \sim Beta(0.25, 1) \end{eqnarray}\]

Note parameter \(l\) in the first line. Hereafter, length = \(l\).

Load result files

small_region_sim_res <- readRDS(file = "../precomputed_results/small_region_sim.Rds")
small_region_sim_res <- small_region_sim_res %>% mutate(method = forcats::fct_recode(method,
  "IHW-Quantile" = "IHW-quantile",
  "IHW-Forest" = "IHW-forest"
))
small_region_sim_res <- small_region_sim_res %>%
  group_by(length, method) %>%
  summarize(
    FDR = mean(FDP, na.rm = TRUE),
    Power = mean(pow, na.rm = TRUE),
    # Power_lower = quantile() #TODO
    n_monte_carlo = sum(!is.na(FDP)),
    pow_se = sd(pow, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n_monte_carlo)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

Plot FDR

small_region_sim_res_FDR <- ggplot(small_region_sim_res, aes(x = length, y = FDR, shape = method, col = method)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = alpha, linetype = 2) +
  guides(
    color = guide_legend(nrow=2, title = "Method", legend.text = element_text(size = 4)),
    shape = guide_legend(nrow=2, title = "Method", legend.text = element_text(size = 4)),
    nrow=2
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 1000, by = 250)) +
  scale_y_log10()
